<td align="center">
<div class="poemtitle">Sundays</div> 
<br>
<a class="byline" href="javascript:goauthor('laughtland')">by Amanda Laughtland</a> <br>
<br>
<br>
<table cellpadding="20" cellspacing="0">
<tr>
<td align="right"><img src="images/sundays.jpg"><br><span class="byartist">Patricia Wallace Jones</span></td>
<td>
Jack-in-the-pulpit always selects<br>
the same text, evidence<br>
<br>
of life after death: homes<br>
for families of owls in the holes<br>
<br>
of dead trees. Jack sets his watch<br>
by the lilies of the valley<br>
<br>
on Mother's Day. He never runs late.<br>
</td>

</tr></table>
</td>
</tr>
